Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a new loss function to improve the discriminative power of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in image classification tasks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the role of loss functions in training deep neural networks and proposes a new loss function to improve the performance of CNNs. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new method for improving the performance of CNNs in image classification tasks, which is a common application of AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of neural networks, specifically CNNs, through the use of a new loss function. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of CNNs in image classification tasks, which is a common application of multimedia analysis.
